```python
@staticmethod
def backward(ctx: Any, grad_output: Tensor) -> Tuple[Tensor, Tensor, None]:
    if ctx.grad_fn is None:
        return (grad_output.sum_to_size(ctx.in_shape), grad_output.sum_to_size(ctx.out_shape), None)
    return (ctx.grad_fn(grad_output.sum_to_size(ctx.in_shape)), ctx.grad_fn(grad_output.sum_to_size(ctx.out_shape)), None)
```

The `forward` method needs to save the gradient function, input shape, and output shape to the context so backward can use them to route gradients appropriately, then simply return the output tensor.

